### Enhancements

* <news item>

### Bug fixes

* Fix Windows CMD.EXE activation failing for environment paths containing `^` (caret) character. The caret was being consumed as an escape character during batch script processing. (#12558)

### Deprecations

* <news item>

### Docs

* <news item>

### Other

* Add comprehensive test cases to characterize environment name validation behavior for Windows special characters (`!`, `=`, `^`, `%`, `(`, `)`). Tests confirm that `!` now works (fixed by PR #14607's batch script rewrite) and identify `^` as broken. (#12558)
